Floating Point Presentation
Numerical Form:
    (-1)^s M 2^(E)
    - Sign bit s determines whether a number is positive or negative
    - Significant M is normally a fractional value in range(1.0, 2.0)
    - Exponent E weighs value by power of two
Encoding:
    - MSB is a sign bit s
    - exp field encodes E (but not equal to E)
    - frac field encodes M (but not equal to M)
 +---+------------+-------------+
 |s  |  exp       |frac         |
 +---+------------+-------------+
